                  <provenance>‘Hic liber est ecclesie sancte Marje de suwicha quem ab ea alienari
                     non licet Quod qui facere presumpserit siue titulum istum dolose deleuerit uel
                     fraudem aliam fecerit quo minus eius sit nisi eidem condigne satisfecerit sit
                     anathema Maranatha Amen’ (<locus from="136v" to="137r">fols. 136<hi
                           rend="superscript">v</hi>–7</locus>, the lower margin). The inscription
                     also appears on <locus from="2r" to="2r">fol. 2</locus>, (from ‘dolose’ only,
                     the remainder on the lost preceding leaf), and <locus from="78v" to="79r">fols.
                           78<hi rend="superscript">v</hi>–9</locus>; in the other examples, ‘hac
                     fiat’ precedes ‘Amen’. <bibl><title>Registrum</title> R.34.21 (173,
                        262),</bibl>
                     <bibl>Ker, <title>MLGB</title> 181.</bibl></provenance>
                  <provenance>‘Homiliae Diui Bernardi in Cantica Canticorum’ (<locus from="1r"
                        to="1r">fol. 1</locus>, upper margin; <date calendar="Gregorian"
                        notBefore="1600" notAfter="1625">s. xvii in.</date>, a St John’s hand).
                  </provenance>
